				<div class=3D"col">
					<h1>Online Board Game Score Sheet</h1>
					<p><strong>This interactive online board game score sheet allows you t=
o keep track the score of up to 10 players. Add the scores automatically an=
d use the built-in timer.</strong></p>
					<p>Enter the score for each player and rund to add them automatically =
in the highlighted bottom&nbsp;row.</p>
					<p>Press the <strong>+</strong>&nbsp;button on the right to add a new =
round to&nbsp;the&nbsp;game.</p>
					<p class=3D"aligncenter">
						<a class=3D"bigButton startTour">Open the settings</a>
						<a class=3D"bigButton how2useToggle">How 2 use?</a>
						<a class=3D"bigButton toggleIntro">Close intro</a>=09
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"col">
					<h2>Settings</h2>
					<p><a class=3D"startTour">Open the settings</a> to adjust and style yo=
ur score sheet. The online <a href=3D"https://scorecount.com/">score&nbsp;c=
ounter</a> works like a score sheet when the "score adder" mode is&nbsp;act=
ive. </p>
					<p>Press the space to start/stop the <strong>timer</strong>. Move your=
 mouse to the bottom right corner of the clock to reset the timer. By defau=
lt the countdown is set to 1 minute but you can adjust this in settings in =
the Period input. You'll have to set the duration in minutes. For example&n=
bsp;enter <em>0.16667</em> if you need to set the timer to 10&nbsp;seconds.=
</p>
					<p>Activate sounds to <strong>sound a horn</strong> when the timer exp=
ires.</p>
					<p>The score sheet is set to 4 players. This value can be set between =
<strong>1&nbsp;to&nbsp;10&nbsp;players</strong>. Change the background imag=
e and adjust the&nbsp;colors.</p>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"col">
					<p class=3D"aligncenter">
						<a class=3D"bigButton toggleIntro">Close intro</a>=09
					</p>
					<p class=3D"aligncenter"><img src=3D"https://scorecount.com/board-game=
/score-sheet.jpg" alt=3D"online board game score sheet" class=3D"max400"></=
p>
					<p class=3D"aligncenter">Forget drawn or printable score sheets. </p>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"wrapHow2Use"><div class=3D"dividerLine how2use"></div><di=
v class=3D"col how2use"><h2>How to use</h2><p>Close this intro text or scro=
ll down to unveil the scoreboard. The gear icon in the menu opens the setti=
ngs where you can experiment with the available options. You can always ref=
resh the page (F5 key) to come back to the default&nbsp;configuartion.</p><=
p>Click the panels to increase the score and other counters and to start/st=
op the timer. Hover the bottom right corner of the panels to reveal additio=
nal shotcuts. </p><p>There art three main modes of operation: the default s=
core counter, the score adder where the porgram automatically adds the scor=
es and the lap timer. </p></div><div class=3D"col how2use"><h2 id=3D"keyboa=
rdCommandsAnchor">Keyboard commands</h2><p><span class=3D"inline"><strong>S=
pace</strong> =E2=80=93 start / stop timer</span><span class=3D"inline"><st=
rong>Esc, Enter</strong> =E2=80=93 exit settings and edit mode</span><span =
class=3D"inline"><strong>E</strong> =E2=80=93 enter edit mode</span><span c=
lass=3D"inline"><strong>R</strong> =E2=80=93 toggle settings</span><span cl=
ass=3D"inline"><strong>Q</strong> =E2=80=93 increase home team score</span>=
<span class=3D"inline"><strong>A</strong> =E2=80=93 decrease home score</sp=
an><span class=3D"inline"><strong>W</strong> =E2=80=93 increase visitor tea=
m score</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>S</strong> =E2=80=93 decrease =
visitor score</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>P</strong> =E2=80=93 inc=
rease period counter</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>I</strong> =E2=80=
=93 home team timeout</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>O</strong> =E2=
=80=93 visitor timeout</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>Y,  U</strong> =
=E2=80=93 increase home&amp;visitor foul/shot</span></p></div><div class=3D=
"col how2use"><p><span class=3D"inline"><strong>H J</strong> =E2=80=93 decr=
ease home&amp;visitor foul/shot</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>T</str=
ong> =E2=80=93 change alternating posession</span><span class=3D"inline"><s=
trong>L</strong> =E2=80=93 toggle overtime</span><span class=3D"inline"><st=
rong>C</strong> =E2=80=93 pause shot clock</span><span class=3D"inline"><st=
rong>X</strong> =E2=80=93 reset shot clock to maximum</span><span class=3D"=
inline"><strong>Z</strong> =E2=80=93 set shot clock to 14 seconds (or value=
 in&nbsp;settings)</span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>V</strong> =E2=80=
=93 edit shot clock value </span><span class=3D"inline"><strong>B</strong> =
=E2=80=93 buzzer sound </span></p><div class=3D"dividerLine how2use"></div>=
<p>This website is using cookies to provide the best user experience. Turn =
them off in your browser settings if you&nbsp;wish to disallow&nbsp;them.</=
p><p><strong>Contact:</strong> <img src=3D"https://scorecount.com/files/con=
t.png" alt=3D"cookie policy"></p></div><div class=3D"dividerLine how2use"><=
/div><div class=3D"col how2use"><h2>The settings</h2><p><strong>Open the me=
nu (=E2=89=A1) in the top right corner of the screen and click the gear ico=
n to access the settings:</strong></p><p><strong>Reset</strong> =E2=80=93 r=
estore the default values with a click<br><strong>Mode</strong> =E2=80=93 b=
eside the default score counter we can add the scores of different rounds a=
nd measure lap times. Start the timer when the lap timer mode is active and=
 click the team/player to record his time.<br><strong>Teams</strong> =E2=80=
=93 add up to 10 players or teams the the game. The default is 2: Homve vs.=
 Visitors.<br><strong>Timer</strong> =E2=80=93 set the timer to show the mi=
nutes and seconds, minutes-seconds-hundredths or automatically show the hun=
dredths when the clock is under one minute. Decide whether to count down or=
 up.<br><strong>Period</strong> =E2=80=93 adjust the period duration and to=
ggle the overtime mark<br><strong>Sounds</strong> =E2=80=93 turn on to soun=
d horn at the end of the period or when the shot clock expires<br><strong>F=
ont</strong> =E2=80=93 beside the default 7-segment display you can use oth=
er font styles</p></div><div class=3D"col how2use"><p><strong>Shot clock</s=
trong> =E2=80=93 a secondary <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shot_=
clock" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"external nofollow">24 second timer</a> is u=
sed to measure the play in basketball. Set up its duration, size, colors an=
d whether you wish to start it automatically with the main timer.<br><stron=
g>Colors</strong> =E2=80=93 activate one of the predefined templates or set=
 your custom 4 colors to style the scoreboard <br><strong>Style</strong> =
=E2=80=93 an advanced field that requires <a href=3D"https://htmlcheatsheet=
.com/css/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"external nofollow">CSS code</a> and all=
ows you to style the board without limitations <br><strong>Images</strong> =
=E2=80=93 add an image background and display the logos of the two opposing=
 teams specifying the URL of the images. You can not upload your image file=
s to our server so I recommend using a thrid party file sharing service suc=
h as <a href=3D"https://postimages.org/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"external =
nofollow">PostImages.org</a> or <a href=3D"https://imgbb.com/" target=3D"_b=
lank" rel=3D"external nofollow">ibb.co</a>. The recommended file format is =
png with transparent background. <br><strong>Adjust</strong> =E2=80=93 set =
the perfect layout for your board adjusting its size, font size and top mar=
gin. Use the <br><strong>Show</strong> =E2=80=93 pick which panels you wish=
 to hide and show. Each panel group has a close button which shows up when =
the settins are open and you hover a display with your mouse.<br>Open the s=
ettings to reorganize the order of the rows and hover the section you would=
 like to move up. Click the top arrows that show up on the right of a panel=
 while hovering it. This way you can move the clock to the top and the scor=
e to the bottom.</p></div><div class=3D"col how2use"><h2>Edit mode</h2><p>T=
oggle edit mode with the pencil icon in the menu. A cursor starts blinking =
in the first score counter when the edit mode is activated. Use your keyboa=
rd to set the values easily. Make sure to enter number values in the counte=
rs, otherwise they will be set to zero. </p><p>The <a href=3D"https://score=
count.com/board-game/#keyboardCommandsAnchor">keyboard shortcuts</a> are di=
sabled when the edit mode is turned on.</p><h2>Full screen</h2><p>Toggle fu=
ll screen mode to hide the browser frame. You can also do this pressing the=
 F11 key in most web browsers. You might need to adjust the zoom and top ma=
rgin in the settings.</p><h2>Save / Broadcast</h2><p>This option collects e=
very current variable on your scoreboard and encodes it in a web link. Ever=
y value that differs from the default will be added as a URL parameter. Thi=
s way you can save your settings and share a game.</p><div class=3D"divider=
Line how2use"></div><p>This website is using third party cookies to collect=
 anonymous visitor analytics and&nbsp;to&nbsp;show tailored&nbsp;ads.</p><p=
><a href=3D"https://scorecount.com/terms-privacy/">Terms and Conditions, Pr=
ivacy&nbsp;Policy</a> | <a href=3D"https://scorecount.com/m/#contact">Conta=
ct</a> | <a href=3D"https://scorecount.com/sitemap/">SiteMap</a> =C2=A9Scor=
eCount.com</p></div></div>
